# NestJS API Layer

- Use global `ValidationPipe` with whitelist and forbidNonWhitelisted.
- Map domain errors to RFC 9457 problem details with stable error codes from `backend_doc/matrices/error_catalog.csv`.
- Propagate correlation ID from incoming header to `RequestSecurityContext` and logs.
- Controllers delegate to application handlers; no business calculations in controllers.
- Check permissions via `requirePermission` before mutations.
- DTOs come from contract schemas; never expose DB entities as responses.
- Register module controllers in `apps/api` composition root, not cross-module deep imports.
